title: Visiting Artist Talk - Jesse Harrod
human: The School of Art and Visual Studies Visiting Artist and Scholar Program is please to present Jesse Harrod
full:
Jesse Harrod

Wednesday, 2/12/2020 @ 6PM, RM 136

Jesse Harrod’s work manipulates and transforms materials to animate their sexual and sensual qualities and explore the intersections among queer kinship, support and sexuality. In their sculptural installations, they work with rope as a pliable linear element that they regard much like a drawing tool, specifically utilizing known making techniques such as macrame in ways that can be understood as simultaneously restraining and support.

This year’s community carving will be Sunday, Oct. 27, from noon to 4 p.m. — coinciding with our Fall Festival, hosted by the Transylvania Young Alumni Council.

Join Tessa and the Lex Center for Creative ReUse for a mid-level crochet course!

This hands-on workshop will guide you through the process of creating your very own Crochet Hexagon Granny Square Cardigan. Tessa will provide step by step instructions on how to crochet a hexagon granny square, form the hexagon into a cardigan, and add finishing touches to your creation. Participants should already know how to do chain, single crochet, and double crochet stitches.

Whether you're interested in crafting your own clothing or looking for a creative outlet, this workshop is for you!

Preview Party for collage artist, Carleton Wing

Carleton Wing shares with us the exploration of his “altered egos” pairing them with his “guardian angels”. A master at using digital collage for storytelling, Wing adds a unique embellishment to each of his “altered egos “and “guardian angels”. According to Wing, to travel with your “altered ego” is a choice but the “guardian angel” is on a more personal level and they choose us.

title: Socrates Cafe
human: Socrates Café is an opportunity to wrestle with the big questions (What is truth? What gives life meaning? Who are we?)  in a facilitated discussion. Based on author Christopher Phillips' (Socrates Café: A Fresh Taste of Philosophy) popular model for public discussion, participants in Socrates Café seek to examine and explore deeply held beliefs in an atmosphere of free, open and friendly exchange. Alternative viewpoints are encouraged and explored, and discussion takes place in an atmosphere of mutual respect and encouragement. No prior knowledge of philosophy is necessary!

Wise Bird Cider's 5 Year Anniversary Party!

Saturday June 8th, 12n - 12a


Mark your calendars, because we’re turning up the party for our 5th

anniversary and you’re invited! From open ‘til close, we’ll have all

kinds of new releases, food & cider specials, entertainment, and

more…!


• 5 ciders, $5 dollars, for 5 hours! (noon-5 PM)

• New Cider Release at noon: Short Stories Vol. 5.

• Dunk Tank Fundraiser supporting “Box 2 Box,” a Lexington

organization using soccer to level the playing field for refugees, new

American students, and their families by empowering them to become

independent thinkers, high-achieving scholars, and productive

citizens.

• Kids Activities

• Other Brothers Band playing from 7-9 PM

• Our first ever Night Owl, featuring a Silent Disco from 10 PM-midnight


We’re so ready to celebrate this milestone—and we wouldn’t be able to

do it without all of you! Cheers to 5 years, and to many more.
